Energy Conversion Drops in Premarket Trading as Sales Plunge, CEO Resigns

-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   M a r t i n
-- 
2011-05-10T13:22:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/energy-conversion-drops-in-premarket-trading-as-sales-plunge-ceo-resigns.html
Energy Conversion Devices Inc. (ENER) , a
maker of flexible solar-power panels, sank in premarket trading
after quarterly sales dropped 71 percent and Chief Executive
Officer and President Mark Morelli resigned.  Energy Conversion fell 18 cents, or 8.7 percent, to $1.57
as of 8:49 a.m. on the Nasdaq Stock Market. Before today, they
had dropped 62 percent over the past year.  Revenue sank to $21.5 million on declining demand in  Europe 
and a net loss of $4.88 per share was recorded as part of a
corporate restructuring,  Auburn Hills , Michigan-based Energy
Conversion said today in a statement.  Jay Knoll, executive vice president and general counsel,
will serve as interim president while the board searches for a
new chief executive.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christopher Martin in  New York  at 
 cmartin11@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at   landberg@bloomberg.net . 